\N<Luda Soldier>Hey there. It's been a while, hasn't it? Were you safe? How
did it go, this mission?

\N<Luda Soldier>Ah... Somehow I managed to return without any serious
injuries. Seems like I'm pretty lucky.

\N<Luda Soldier>It was your first combat mission, right? Heh, what do you
think?

\N<Luda Soldier>What's there to say? We're all practically amateurs, aren't
we? Just until recently we were living carefree in this
town. Then those Luda guys suddenly forced us into military
service...

\N<Luda Soldier>Hey, hey, don't say anything too rash. It'd be trouble if a
superior officer heard you.
\N<Luda Soldier>I know, but I gotta vent a little or I can't stand it.

\N<Luda Soldier>Well, maybe the Luda folks understand our gripes as citizen
soldiers, and that's why they've prepared 'that' as a way
for us to let off steam.
\N<Luda Soldier>You're going too, right?
\N<Luda Soldier>Of course. I couldn't keep doing this job otherwise.
